     fhir:documentation [ fhir:v "Indicates status of a care gap. For all [open, closed, and prospective gaps], three seperate status parameters must be provided. For a positive proportion measure, gap means the patient is not in the numerator. For an inverse (negative) proportion measure (e.g., Diabetes: Hemoglobin A1c (HbA1c) Poor Control (> 9%)), gap means the patient is in the numerator." ] ;
